### Figma-to-Code Mapping Rules

- **Colors**
  - Map Figma “Semantic Colors” to CSS variables: primary, secondary, accent, destructive, background, foreground, border, input, ring, card/popover pairs.
  - For charts, map series to `--chart-1..5`.

- **Typography**
  - Use Inter for UI text, JetBrains Mono for code-like text.
  - Sizes/weights: leverage Tailwind `text-sm`, `text-base`, `font-semibold`, etc.

- **Spacing & Layout**
  - Use Tailwind spacing scale. Constrain content with Tailwind `container` (2rem padding, 1400px at 2xl).

- **Components**
  - Prefer existing shadcn/ui atoms/molecules. Add new ones in `src/components/ui` using Radix primitives + Tailwind + `cva`.
  - Keep variants minimal and token-driven. Use `cn` to merge classes.

- **Icons**
  - Use `lucide-react` exclusively. Import icons by name at usage sites.

- **Dark Mode**
  - Ensure dual tokens for readable contrast. Test by applying `.dark` class.

### Contribution Checklist (Design System)

- Add new tokens to `globals.css` and map in `tailwind.config.js` if needed.
- Build new UI as shadcn-compatible components under `src/components/ui`.
- Use `cva` for variants and `cn` for class merging.
- Keep all colors referencing token variables, not hard-coded hex.
- If adding images, store under `frontend/public` and, if using `<Image>`, add domains in `next.config.js`.

### MCP Designer Prompt (for Figma integration)

Use this prompt when asking the MCP to generate code from selected Figma nodes:

```text
Generate React (Next.js App Router, TypeScript) components using shadcn/ui and Tailwind.
- Style strictly with Tailwind classes mapped to our tokens (hsl(var(--...))).
- Use our token names: primary, secondary, accent, destructive, background, foreground, border, input, ring, card/popover, chart-1..5; radius via var(--radius).
- Use Inter font (via next/font) and honor dark mode via .dark token set.
- Wrap primitives with shadcn/ui components where available (button, input, card, dialog, dropdown, tabs, sheet, table, etc.).
- Use lucide-react icons by name, size 16–24px as needed.
- Keep responsive behavior via Tailwind breakpoints; container width 1400px at 2xl with 2rem padding.
- Do not introduce custom CSS files; only Tailwind utilities and existing token classes.
- Place new components in src/components/ui with cva variants as necessary.
```